ePDFView Installation Instructions
===================================

PREREQUISITES
=============

Required:
  * GTK4 >= 4.0.0
  * Poppler with GLib bindings >= 0.5.0
  * GLib >= 2.8.0
  * Meson >= 0.50.0
  * Ninja build tool
  * pkg-config

Optional:
  * CUPS (for printing support)
  * CppUnit (for running tests)

INSTALLING DEPENDENCIES
=======================

Arch Linux:
  $ sudo pacman -S gtk4 poppler-glib meson ninja cups base-devel

Ubuntu/Debian:
  $ sudo apt install libgtk-4-dev libpoppler-glib-dev meson \
                     ninja-build libcups2-dev build-essential gettext

Fedora/RHEL:
  $ sudo dnf install gtk4-devel poppler-glib-devel meson \
                     ninja-build cups-devel gcc-c++ gettext

openSUSE:
  $ sudo zypper install gtk4-devel poppler-glib-devel meson \
                        ninja cups-devel gcc-c++ gettext-tools

BASIC INSTALLATION
==================

1. Get the source code:
   
   From Git:
     $ git clone https://github.com/JotaRandom/epdfview.git
     $ cd epdfview
   
   From release tarball:
     $ tar xzf epdfview-0.3.0.tar.gz
     $ cd epdfview-0.3.0

2. Configure the build:
   
   $ meson setup builddir

3. Compile:
   
   $ meson compile -C builddir

4. Install (system-wide):
   
   $ sudo meson install -C builddir

5. Run:
   
   $ epdfview

INSTALLATION OPTIONS
====================

Install to /usr instead of /usr/local:

  $ meson setup builddir --prefix=/usr
  $ meson compile -C builddir
  $ sudo meson install -C builddir

Install to custom location:

  $ meson setup builddir --prefix=/opt/epdfview
  $ meson compile -C builddir
  $ sudo meson install -C builddir

Install to home directory (no sudo needed):

  $ meson setup builddir --prefix=$HOME/.local
  $ meson compile -C builddir
  $ meson install -C builddir
  $ export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"

BUILD OPTIONS
=============

Disable CUPS printing support:

  $ meson setup builddir -Dcups=disabled

Debug build:

  $ meson setup builddir --buildtype=debug

Release build (optimized):

  $ meson setup builddir --buildtype=release

View all options:

  $ meson configure builddir

RUNNING WITHOUT INSTALLING
===========================

After building, you can run directly from the build directory:

  $ ./builddir/src/epdfview

UNINSTALLING
============

From the build directory:

  $ sudo ninja -C builddir uninstall

Or manually remove files listed in:

  builddir/meson-logs/install-log.txt

TROUBLESHOOTING
===============

GTK4 not found:
  * Install GTK4 development packages
  * Verify: pkg-config --modversion gtk4

Poppler not found:
  * Install Poppler GLib development packages  
  * Verify: pkg-config --modversion poppler-glib

CUPS not found (optional):
  * Install CUPS development packages
  * Or disable with: -Dcups=disabled

Icons missing at runtime:
  * Icons installed to: PREFIX/share/pixmaps/
  * Application searches: /usr/share/pixmaps and /usr/local/share/pixmaps
  * Reinstall or copy icons manually

Build fails:
  * Clean build: rm -rf builddir && meson setup builddir
  * Check dependencies are installed
  * Read error messages carefully

ADDITIONAL DOCUMENTATION
========================

For more detailed installation instructions and troubleshooting:

  See docs/INSTALLATION.md for comprehensive guide
  See docs/GTK4_MIGRATION_SUMMARY.md for technical details
  See CONTRIBUTING for development setup

PACKAGING
=========

For distribution packagers:

  Recommended install prefix: /usr
  Desktop file: data/epdfview.desktop
  Icons: data/*.png, data/epdfview.svg
  Translations: po/*.po (22 languages)
  Man page: data/epdfview.1

Example for package:

  $ meson setup builddir --prefix=/usr
  $ meson compile -C builddir  
  $ DESTDIR=$pkgdir meson install -C builddir

